<article>
    <h1>How the smart park&#xAD;ing sys&#xAD;tem works</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201231/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-31"><time>2020-12-31</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>From Mon­day, a trial of the smart park­ing sys­tem will be car­ried out at one carpark com­pris­ing 1,000 park­ing spa­ces. Here are the new fea­tures.</p>
    <p>1</p>
    <p>Bar­rier-free en­try and exit to the carpark</p>
    <p>• There will be no gantry bar­ri­ers at the carpark en­trance and exit as ve­hi­cle plates are reg­is­tered via cam­eras.</p>
    <p>2</p>
    <p>More pay­ment op­tions</p>
    <p>• Mo­torists park­ing short term can pay for their park­ing charges via credit or debit card through the Park­ing@HDB app.</p>
    <p>3 New over­head light in­di­ca­tors</p>
    <p>• Green means spa­ces are avail­able for short-term park­ing, and am­ber means spa­ces are re­served for sea­son park­ing. The light in­di­ca­tor will be switched off for oc­cu­pied spa­ces.</p>
    <p>4 In-app alerts for vis­it­ing mo­torists</p>
    <p>• Vis­i­tors who have down­loaded the Park­ing@HDB app will re­ceive an au­to­mated in-app alert at the start and end of their park­ing ses­sion that will also in­form them of their in­curred charges.</p>
    <p>• They will also be in­formed to shift their ve­hi­cle if they park in an unau­tho­rised space. 5 Flex­i­ble al­lo­ca­tion of park­ing spa­ces</p>
    <p>• Park­ing spa­ces will be au­to­mat­i­cally al­lo­cated be­tween sea­son park­ing and vis­i­tor park­ing to meet vary­ing de­mands on a real-time ba­sis, based on carpark us­age data col­lected over time.</p>
    <p>• This fea­ture will be rolled out at a later date.</p>

